Legion of Heroes <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarkmournsoulraver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkmourn Soulraver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/14/02 1:23:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10667.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoM</span><hr size=1> I'm the SK that's up there right now (not bound, just not zoning out).  The only reasons I have for staying are 1) It's the best reason in the world you can have for not helping &quot;friends&quot; with some boring camp, and 2) my in-game wife is bound there and I'd like to help her any way I can.<br>
<br>
To be blunt, the zone sucks if you are all alone (and not a shaman).  Monks can definitely solo better than I can, but the only mobs you'll be able to kill reliably will be the forest mobs.  I have to fear kite them, and it takes the majority of my mana bar to kill one.  They have a ton of hp's, hit pretty hard (some with deadly poison), and most con light blue to me at 57 and give next to no xp.  And to top it all off, they only drop squires.<br>
<br>
A melee, slower, and healer can do most of the mobs, but as has been stated, the throne drops are so rare that the only real benefit you'll get is xp.  If I get lucky I'll get a really nice SK only bracer (better than all 3 quest types), but even that takes 2 thrones and a crown.  To get any of the armor that requires boxes, forget it unless you can buy a doll.  I would bet you could be up there for 6 months and not get enough for one box...and when you finally do, odds are it will be for a different class. <p>Darkmourn D'Estrellas <BR>Troll Shadowknight <BR><img src=http://www.lanset.com/soulcatcher/images/deadppl_e0.gif ><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustamen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stamen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><--Dies more then Ganon</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/14/02 2:34:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10667.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoM</span><hr size=1> getting a doll is not out of the question, i know quite a few monk boxes were made while it was still easy, hell i think i still have a monk doll in my bank.  also enchanter dolls are very common, i still have 4 of those.  so just check around, maybe you could get the armor you want without as much work as you think.<br>
